---
import Base from '../layouts/Base.astro';
import ContactLinks from '../components/ContactLinks.astro';
// Copy pending final review with Shahar before deploy.
---

<Base
  title="About | Shahar Kozniak"
  description="Who Shahar Kozniak is, how he works, and what he's focused on."
>
  <header class="page-header">
    <p class="eyebrow" data-reveal>Profile</p>
    <h1 data-reveal style="--reveal-delay: 80ms">
      About <span class="gradient-text">me</span>
    </h1>
  </header>

  <div class="prose" data-reveal>
    <p>
      I'm Shahar Kozniak, a backend and AI engineer. My work sits where
      software meets manual labor: I look for the processes that eat
      someone's hours every week and turn them into systems.
    </p>

    <h2>How I work</h2>
    <p>
      I plan before I build. Unknowns get mapped first and resolved in order
      of risk, decisions run on data rather than gut feeling, and I hold a
      high bar for what leaves my hands. I'd rather ship fewer things that
      hold up than many things that almost do.
    </p>

    <h2>What I'm focused on</h2>
    <ul>
      <li>
        Automation that pays for itself, like a platform that turned a
        multi-day manual server audit into a background job.
      </li>
      <li>
        Working with AI seriously. Agents and AI tooling are part of how I
        build now, and I invest in getting better at them constantly.
      </li>
      <li>
        Range on purpose: backend platforms, IoT hardware, internal tools
        and customer-facing web, with the same discipline across all of
        them.
      </li>
    </ul>

    <h2>Get in touch</h2>
    <p>
      Email is fastest. If you're hiring for a role where automation,
      reliability and ownership matter, I want to hear about it.
    </p>
  </div>

  <div class="contact" data-reveal>
    <ContactLinks />
  </div>
</Base>

<style>
  .page-header {
    padding-block: var(--space-2xl);
    display: flex;
    flex-direction: column;
    gap: var(--space-sm);
  }

  .page-header h1 {
    font-size: var(--text-title);
  }

  .contact {
    margin-block: var(--space-2xl);
    padding-top: var(--space-xl);
    border-top: 1px solid var(--line);
  }
</style>
